<h2>Bundles</h2>

<h3>Bundles that come pre-installed</h3>

<h3>Installing new bundles</h3>
Currently not all features of bundles are supported. Currently supported features include snippets and themes.<p/>

Redcar is installed under the ruby-gems directory. Depending on your platform and how you installed Redcar (all users or single user) the default directory may be different.<p/>

Redcar should not be running to complete this installation.<p/>

Open a command shell and go to the ~/.redcar/cache directory. <p/>
Delete the file textmate_bundles.cache.<p/>
Copy the tmbundle file to the /usr/lib/ruby/gems/ruby-version/gems/redcar-redcar-version/textmate/Bundles. <p/>

Restart Redcar and it will rebuild the bundles cache file. This could take a while.<p/>


 
 

